{"TopicId":155198,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Right-Click rotates camera very crazy","CreatedByName":"Panakotta00","CreatedById":173927,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-18T16:45:58Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Panakotta00","CreatedById":173927,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-18T16:45:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I right click in flight or anywhere, my camera rotates very crazy! With right click I doesn\u0027t mean something like \u0022drag\u0027n drop\u0022, noooooo, I mean a normal right click! And the rotation comes before the real \u0022right-click\u0022 is executed, that means, \u0022righ-click -\u0026gt; rotate -\u0026gt; click to open part gui\u0022. Can any body help me?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nOS: Windows 10 64-bit\u003Cbr\u003E\nKSP: v1.2.2.1622-64-bit\u00A0(unmodded)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"diomedea","CreatedById":93700,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-19T11:02:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis seems as if the right-click was binded to a camera control in the settings. You may check if something shows in the Settings/Game/Camera section (both keys and axes). Can\u0027t tell how a mouse click could be registered with settings, it never does on my system, but your configuration could possibly allow something different.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo let us diagnose your issue, would be best to examine your settings.cfg file (please upload and link). Also output_log file, please, it always helps. I\u0027d also like to find a better description of the kind of rotation the camera shows (e.g., it rotates same way if the pointer is left/right/above/below the center? rotation goes with same speed all the time, or changes with cursor position?); if you can, uploading a video showing the issue would make things more evident.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Panakotta00","CreatedById":173927,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-19T13:33:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy Data:\u003Cbr\u003E\nVideo:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/ai6eq07sngu9t1l/KSP%20right%20click%20error.mp4?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/ai6eq07sngu9t1l/KSP right click error.mp4?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nLog:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/nlkapu3w0vtaf3v/KSP.log?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/nlkapu3w0vtaf3v/KSP.log?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nConfig:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/op0z27h9qujdpjw/settings.cfg?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/op0z27h9qujdpjw/settings.cfg?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd no, i think ther isn\u0027t something in the configuration.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-19T14:03:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you try with a new save please, it looks like you are using a modded save.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022 id=\u0022ips_uid_5319_4\u0022\u003E\n[ERR 14:27:46.692] Cannot find a Module of typename \u0027InterVesselManager\u0027\n\n[ERR 14:27:46.693] ScenarioModule is null.\n\n[ERR 14:27:46.693] Cannot find a Module of typename \u0027KPBSScenario\u0027\n\n[ERR 14:27:46.694] ScenarioModule is null.\n\n[ERR 14:27:46.695] Cannot find a Module of typename \u0027SCANcontroller\u0027\n\n[ERR 14:27:46.696] ScenarioModule is null.\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKBPS is from Kerbal Planetary Base Systems.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso what mouse do you have and have you changed the mouse polling rate?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Panakotta00","CreatedById":173927,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-19T14:11:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222927158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155198\u0022 data-ipsquote-